
    MZANSI President Jacob Zuma announced on Tuesday that he would be appointing a commission of inquiry into allegations of state capture by the Gupta family.In
December, the High Court ordered Zuma to appoint a commission of inquiry within
30 days, which would be headed by a judge selected solely by Mogoeng.Chief
Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng, recommended Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo to head
the commission of inquiry as ordered by previous Public Protector Thuli
